Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel). Pop them onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, trim the @aubergine{1/2} then slice into rounds approximately 2cm thick. Slice the @halloumi{250%g} into 3 slices per person, then place them into a small #bowl{} of cold water and leave to soak. Halve the @glazed burger buns{2}.

Pop the aubergine onto another baking tray. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer and roast the aubergine on the middle shelf of your oven until soft and golden, ~{20-25%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, mix together the @onion marmalade{20%g} and @harissa paste{25%g} in a small bowl. Set your harissa relish aside.

> Add less harissa paste if you don't like heat.

When 10 mins of roasting time remain, remove the halloumi slices from the cold water. Pop them onto a #plate{} lined with #kitchen paper{} and pat them dry. Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the halloumi and fry until golden, ~{2-3%mins} each side. Remove from the heat once cooked.

Just before serving, pop your burger buns onto the aubergine baking tray to warm through, ~{2-3%mins}. When ready, lay the halloumi slices on the warmed bun bases. Top with the aubergine rounds, then the @wild rocket{20%g}. Spread a generous amount of harissa relish on the bun lids and then place on top. Serve up your burgers with the potato wedges alongside. Enjoy!